The paper focuses on using deep learning algorithms for object detection in underwater environments, specifically for the purpose of detecting and removing marine litter using autonomous underwater vehicles (AUVs). This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) categories, as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of a large dataset and evaluation of different algorithms, which could also place it in the information retrieval (cs.IR) category.
